    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Dact1 is present at forebrain synapses\"\n- \"This staining, which was absent from Dact1-/- HCNs (Fig 1B), colocalized with synaptic markers, including at punctate intensities of the excitatory postsynaptic marker protein PSD95 likely to correspond to postsynaptic sites (Fig 1C-H). Supporting a postsynaptic localization for Dact1, immunoblotting of subcellular fractions derived from forebrain cortical cultures revealed that recombinantly expressed FLAG-Dact1 co-partitioned with PSD95 in postsynaptic, as opposed to presynaptic, fractions (Fig 1I).\". Experimental description: - \"Dact1 is a postsynaptic protein required for dendrite, spine, and excitatory synapse development in the mouse forebrain\"",
